<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_96283174-6429-41b5-ac61-bbe48f3a81e7" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10b"/></meta><sptc>10.2.18</sptc><title id="_deec00f1-40c2-4e26-80ab-eb8c0a4ea8ec">Unenclosed showers</title><archive-num>New for 2022</archive-num><subclause id="_244b7431-ad4a-4eda-a255-9f7f8f1a51e4" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_162335b6-d9cc-4d37-ba36-897227886aee">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Unenclosed showers must be constructed as follows:</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_d840ecb0-bbf5-4cf8-b8fe-4c60a9d0cea3">A <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4735_0.5.0.xml#_2fb1baed-5210-4b6f-a0d1-49efc309b967" id="_e604055c-02e0-464d-bf34-e174f8e32194" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">waterstop</xref> must be installed a minimum horizontal distance of 1500 mm from the shower rose.</li><li id="_29308f51-9274-4ed6-9a9c-749651f93538">The vertical leg of the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4735_0.5.0.xml#_2fb1baed-5210-4b6f-a0d1-49efc309b967" id="_07cc19a1-a874-4d15-a183-bf8173eb547e" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">waterstop</xref> must finish—<ol><li>flush with the top surface of the floor (see <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4739_0.17.0.xml#_fbd2eecd-25bf-4cf6-b63e-89285fac4845" id="_24205e97-33ff-4e06-aebb-ac2563e1f633" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 10.2.18</xref>); and</li><li>where the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4735_0.5.0.xml#_2fb1baed-5210-4b6f-a0d1-49efc309b967" id="_ee58a8c0-6ec4-4791-ac2c-dbeeee513849" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">waterstop</xref> intersects with a wall or is joined—<ol><li>the junction must be <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1519_0.5.0.xml#_02296d09-c6a7-41f4-a398-1f059045818c" id="_13a18d1a-0466-4108-87f7-8a4228d7e5a9" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">waterproof</xref>; or</li><li>the whole <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1523_27.0.0.xml#_28f0fa3d-c51f-4413-8274-97824adf4971" id="_c09a0fe2-45c9-493c-9a77-187bc2fb85f3" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">wet area</xref> floor must be waterproofed and drained to a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4659_0.3.0.xml#_3aa47b15-8473-4ba3-ae33-cf9b2d99ad0b" id="_a1cb48b3-d494-47e1-b1a4-dcd936a99c7f" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">floor waste</xref> as for the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1460_0.12.0.xml#_6aa99639-a955-4628-bc59-dabb3bfc8118" id="_ca35c95b-2766-41bd-a117-be75ab068aa0" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">shower area</xref>.</li></ol></li></ol></li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_97aa47a8-ea32-4ba3-b859-790c7740f5fb" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_cc2cf067-2ac6-464e-8c87-e20e73834690">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>In the case of (1)(b)(ii)(B), at doorways, where the height of the tiling angle needs to be adjusted for tiling purposes, the angle must be fixed with a sealant compatible with the waterproofing <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4651_0.4.0.xml#_6e2c1aaa-5993-4850-908f-ac4007e94535" id="_e052359d-c169-4986-a77c-591ce5a2021a" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">membrane</xref> without damaging the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4652_0.8.0.xml#_9786edfd-014d-4144-bb1c-bc7b6a43aa5a" id="_ee2256c7-f14b-4bfc-8b3c-bf0b506fa07b" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">waterproofing system</xref>.</p></subclause><image-reference author="Brandon Kiem" conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4739_0.17.0.xml" dateTime="2021-02-26T16:42:41" id="_fbd2eecd-25bf-4cf6-b63e-89285fac4845" type="insert"><num/><title id="_76c268f8-49f1-42e1-b30b-f146a97ebe9f"/></image-reference></clause>